author: Jose Martinez
title: Jose Bautista (Blue Jays OF) Hits Three-Run Homer, Unleashes Epic Bat Flip
text:
Following a strange, weird, utterly ridiculous top of the 7th inning where the Texas Rangers took a 3-2 lead over the Toronto Blue Jays in Game 5 of the 2015 ALDS after the umpires ruled this play as a throwing error by catcher Russell Martin .
Who gets the RBI? #rangers #bluejays #alds https://t.co/pqI4zsNlcD
— Yahoo Sports (@YahooSports) October 14, 2015 While it appears that the ball struck the bat/hand of Shin-Soo Choo , the umpires didn't change their call and the Rogers Centre absolutely lost it, throwing everything within sight onto the field. As karma would have it, the Jays evened the score in the bottom half of the inning following three errors by the Rangers. Then, Jose Bautista came to the plate with two on base and delivered the knockout blow.
Your browser does not support iframes. Did you see that?! Don't ask us what! You know exactly what we're talking about! DID YOU SEE THAT BAT FLIP?!?!
#BatFlip forever on loop. #OwnOctober https://t.co/bGMRSvGVwL
— MLB (@MLB) October 14, 2015 The whole world saw it!
That bat flip though. #JoeyBatFlip pic.twitter.com/BNcy2dNrcE
— Baseball Tonight (@BBTN) October 14, 2015 Also that’s the bat flip by which all others will be judged.
— Greg (@grogg) October 14, 2015 PLAY THAT BAT FLIP ON LOOP AT MY FUNERAL
— Chris Lund (@chrisjlund) October 14, 2015 I'm going to tattoo a GIF of that Jose Bautista bat flip on my face
— Jonah Keri (@jonahkeri) October 14, 2015 In a win or go home game, it would've been a shame to see the Jays get bounced from postseason play on a controversial call. Joey Bats, though, came to the rescue and punctuated the moment with one of the most over-the-top bat flips you will ever see. But, you know what? It was totally worth it.
